The Passenger Rail Agency of South Africa s board has been dissolved in parliament on Wednesday. The board was briefing the parliamentary portfolio committee on transport on the status of Metrorail. Since yesterday Members of Parliament had called for the board to be removed after it was hauled over the coals for being corrupt and their handling of former acting CEO Collins Letsoalo s firing. We have been fired said a board member in parliament. This is a developing story. TMG Digital/The Times Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share